translated: Dymling, Ebbe Samuel, MA in Law and Philosophy, Mayor, War judge, Karlskrona, born on August 29, 1894 in Gothenburg, son of district-provost Karl Andersson and Anna Dymling. He was married twice, first in 1930 to Mary Strömberg who died in 1933, and then in 1941 to Selma Särner, born Hellquist. — He completed his high school studies in Halmstad in 1913, and obtained a BA in Philosophy from Lund University in 1918, and an MA in Law in 1922. He served in the court in Tingstjg. from 1924 to 1926, was acting clerk in the Court of Appeal for Skåne and Blekinge in 1926, became an assessor in 1930, and has been a mayor of Karlskrona since 1933. He has also been the military judge for the Karlskrona naval base and the Karlskrona coastal artillery regiment since 1937. He was the deputy chairman of the county labor board for Blekinge from 1945, and the chairman of the county temperance commission in Blekinge since 1939. He has been awarded the Order of the North Star (RNO).
